<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence from Step Change in Safety Helicopter Safety Steering Group and Helicopter Task Group (HCS0009)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">from</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> Step Change in Safety Helicopter Safety Steering Group and Helicopter Task Group</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> (HCS0009)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:14.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Executive Summary</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.07pt; padding-left:6.93pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Step Change in Safety is the UK based partnership organisation, established by the industry, with the remit to make the UK </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the safest Oil and Gas Exploration and Production province in the world</span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It is tripartite in nature with employers, regulators, workforce and their representative trades unions working collectively towards this common aim.  </span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The Helicopter Safety </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Steering Group (HSSG) is one of five steering groups established by Step Change in Safety. It has the remit to work proactively to identify and address cross-industry issues around helicopter safety, related to helicopter operations in the UK oil and gas i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ndustry.</span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Helicopter operators, oil and gas operators and contractors, offshore trade unions RMT and Unite, the pilots’ union BALPA, the regulators HSE and CAA and the industry trade association Oil &amp; Gas UK are all represented at a senior level on the ste</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ering group. </span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Its purpose is to act on behalf of the industry to steer priorities and act as a communications focal point for sharing information, advice and learning across the industry and with other stakeholders, on helicopter safety matters, including</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> assisting with the implementation of recommendations from any related Air Accidents Investigation Branch (AAIB) inquiries</span><span style="color:#018ac0; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 23.8pt; padding-left:11.65pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The HSSG worked throughout 2013 following the two ditchings of EC225 aircraft, in liaison with the helicopter manufacturers and the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> helicopter operating companies, in order to ensure that the root causes of those failures were established and effective remedial action taken to allow the aircraft to safely return to service</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 23.8pt; padding-left:11.65pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Following the Shetland helicopter crash in August 2013, HSSG </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">took the decision on behalf of the industry to temporarily suspend flying operations of Super Puma aircraft until more information became available as to the likely cause. This “Time Out for Safety” allowed the helicopter operators time to review their ope</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rating procedures and maintenance regimes in the light of the known evidence and allow a progressive return to flying with confidence.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 23.8pt; padding-left:11.65pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Subsequently a dedicated Helicopter Task Group has been established reporting to the HSSG in order to monitor progress w</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ith the Shetland crash accident investigation, engage with the various inquiries and reviews that have been set up, and communicate and engage with the workforce.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 23.8pt; padding-left:11.65pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This submission summarises the work of the HSSG and HTG to date, and the likely agenda going</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> forward. As such it principally focusses on the role of industry in improving offshore helicopter safety,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">but makes comment on the effectiveness of the regulatory regime.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">      </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Step Change in Safety</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Step Change in Safety was founded in 1997 by the Oil</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and Gas industry trade associations with the aim of reducing all the UK offshore Oil and Gas industry injury rate by 50%.  By 2002 a new vision was created: “The UK is the safest place to work in the worldwide oil and gas industry by 2010” and Step Change</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> moved to operate under the PILOT umbrella.</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In 2010, we launched our five year Strategic Plan 2010-2015, setting out how we would go about making the UK the safest oil and gas province in the world.  As we strive to deliver further improvements in safety </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">performance, it is of vital importance that our industry understands the challenges and barriers which stand between us and delivering our vision.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.2.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">As a tripartite body – representing the workforce, regulator and employers - Step Change is committed to inv</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">olving everyone in safety improvement.  It is this broad stakeholder base that makes the Step Change group effective across the whole industry and seen globally as an example of best practice.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.2.4</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We want Step Change to be the driver for change in a numb</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">er of key areas:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">•</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We must have strong and sustainable leadership in health and safety.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">•</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We must have the competence to identify hazards and ensure that risks are properly controlled.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">•</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We must have a workforce that is fully engaged in health and safety.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">•</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">must raise standards and continually improve our health and safety performance.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">•</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We must have effective asset integrity management.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">•</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We must have effective systems of communication for health and safety issues.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">     </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">History of the HSSG</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.3.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The HSSG was formed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> under the auspices of Step Change in Safety in 2010, taking over from the work done by the Oil and Gas UK Helicopter Task Group which had been created to address cross-industry issues around helicopter safety, specifically those arising from the fatal hel</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">icopter crash off the north-east coast of Scotland on 1 April 2009.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.3.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Represented on that task group were companies directly involved in the fatal accident, Oil &amp; Gas UK's Board and Council members, the offshore workforce, helicopter operators, HM Coastguar</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d, Grampian Police and trade unions.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.3.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Its purpose was to act on behalf of the industry as a communications focal point for sharing information, advice and learning across the industry and with other stakeholders on matters arising from this and other helic</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">opter accidents, including assisting with the implementation of any recommendations from the Air Accidents Investigation Branch (AAIB) inquiries.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">1.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">        </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Representation on HSSG</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.4.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">HSSG is made up of senior level representatives from the helicopter operator</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s, oil and gas operators and contractors, the offshore trade unions Unite and RMT, the pilots union BALPA, the CAA and HSE and the industry trade body, Oil and Gas UK.  The HSSG meets six times per year.  Membership of HSSG is reviewed annually to ensure i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t continues to best represent the UK offshore sector.  HSSG has 2 co-chairs, one from a helicopter operator, the other from an oil company.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">1.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">     </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">HSSG Response to the EC225 ditchings in 2012</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.5.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In May and October 2012 there were two precautionary ditchings </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of EC225 aircraft.  The aircraft were forced to ditch because of failures of a shaft in the main gearbox which drove the two oil pumps providing gearbox lubrication.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.5.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Following the second incident the aircraft were suspended from offshore flights by the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">CAA.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.5.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">HSSG was actively involved in liaison with Eurocopter the helicopter manufacturer and the helicopter operators, following the investigation and engaging their own independent experts to assess the findings and the proposed programme of remedial actio</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ns.  This included the facilitation of visits by members of HSSG and others to the Eurocopter factory to see manufacture and testing of components at first hand.  A wide range of communication materials were prepared to enable communication with the workfo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rce and open “town hall” presentations were carried out in Aberdeen.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">1.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">     </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Response to the Shetland Crash </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.6.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">When the Eurocopter Super Puma L2 crashed on approach to Sumburgh on 23 August 2013, killing four passengers workforce confidence fell even f</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">urther.  HSSG took the lead in the response and made the decision to temporarily suspend flying operations of all Super Puma aircraft until more information became available as to the likely cause.  Once it began to become clear that there had been no tech</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nical failure of the aircraft, HSSG was heavily involved in providing information to the workforce, facilitating management visits offshore, heliport and offshore briefings and publishing “Frequently Asked Questions” (FAQs) to keep the workforce informed.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">1.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">     </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Establishment of the HTG</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.7.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The current Helicopter Task Group is a smaller sub-group of HSSG that has been established to provide support to the HSSG in managing the response to the Shetland Helicopter Accident and to ensure that the necessary r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">esource and focus is available to meet the short term workload.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.7.2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The scope of HTG is to:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Monitor the progress of the investigation and respond quickly to any developments</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Ensure the production of appropriate support material</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Collect views and workforce feedback </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Consider any immediate confidence building/safety improvements that can be made</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Inform the proposed independent reviews and inquiries</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.7.3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">To date HTG have been preparing monthly newsletters for distribution offshore</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, carried out a briefing to the Step Change Elected Safety Representatives meeting in November and created a series of factsheets describing, amongst other things, how helicopters are certified in respect of evacuation and escape and how the content and qu</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ality of offshore survival training and helicopter underwater escape training is overseen at an industry level.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.7.4    Input has been provided to the CAA review and the Task Group are engaged with the helicopter manufacturer and the manufacturer of pass</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">enger survival equipment.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><img src="data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAXAAAAACCAYAAABBhIdBAAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAAARnQU1BAACxjwv8YQUAAAAJcEhZcwAADsMAAA7DAcdvqGQAAAAtSURBVEhLY2CAgP+jeDQMRtPAaBoYTQNDKg1Ai+9RajQERkNgNARGQ2DIhQAALwlsojXyHXMAAAAASUVORK5CYII=" width="368" height="2" alt="" style="margin-left:84.5pt; margin-top:7.25pt; position:absolute; z-index:1" /></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">How Safe are Helicopter Flights?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 71.85pt; text-indent:-43.5pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">2.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">HSSG believes that helicopters remain the safest and most efficient way to transport personnel to offshore installations.  However due to their complexity and the conditions in which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">they operate it is well recognised that, statistically, helicopters have a lower safety performance than large commercial fixed wing aircraft.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 71.85pt; text-indent:-43.5pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">2.2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Nevertheless, HSSG understands, from statistics published by Oil and Gas UK amongst others, that safety perf</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ormance in the North Sea leads the rest of the world by some margin, in spite of recent accidents.  HSSG recognises that workforce confidence has been badly shaken by those accidents and that more needs to be done to improve the safety of offshore helicopt</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">er operations.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">What steps can be taken by industry to improve the  safety of offshore flights?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 71.85pt; text-indent:-43.5pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Huge improvements in capability and safety performance have been made over the past 30 years or so. Many initiatives from the mandatory use of survival s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">uits to the implementation of improved communications equipment and “virtual radar” systems have been driven by the offshore industry who have supported safety research activities in conjunction with CAA and others.   Modern helicopters also have much impr</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">oved single engine performance, fault tolerance, avionics and flight information, autopilot capability and flight data monitoring (including Health and Usage Monitoring Systems (HUMS)).</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 71.85pt; text-indent:-43.5pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3.2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">However, HSSG takes the view that there is much more that can be </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">done to improve the consistency with which the full capability of modern aircraft can be used to improve safety of operation.  In contrast with the situation for large fixed wing aircraft, it would seem that individual operators have different ways of oper</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ating the same helicopter type, through the use of their own, independently derived, operations manuals. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 71.85pt; text-indent:-43.5pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3.3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We believe that with good co-operation between the helicopter manufacturers and each of the helicopter operators, there is the potential to achie</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ve a level of consistency akin to that already present in the commercial fixed wing sector. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 71.85pt; text-indent:-43.5pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 71.85pt; text-indent:-43.5pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3.4</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Directionally in the long term HSSG sees significant potential to improve safety by modernising the fleet to provide more aircraft with enhanced capabilities </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and safety features, and utilising these to the maximum effect.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">How could legislation and regulations be improved?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 71.85pt; text-indent:-43.5pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">4.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">HSSG believes that it is important that the high standards achieved by UK (and Norway) are not undermined by lower standards elsewhere</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in Europe.  For example, the requirement to have Vibration Health Monitoring (or HUMS) fitted to aircraft operating offshore is not universal across Europe.  Similarly the CAA have only limited powers of enforcement on aircraft operating within the UK, bu</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t registered elsewhere, and it is important that a “level playing field” is maintained if standards are to be maintained.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">How effective are existing regulators, including the European Aviation Safety Agency (EASA) in ensuring that recommendations to im</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">prove safety are implemented?</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 71.85pt; text-indent:-43.5pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">5.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">HSSG believes that the industry needs a regulator that is competent, professional and properly resourced.  CAA should be seen to be more visible, active and engaged with the offshore industry.  The strength and visibility</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of their immediate response to the Shetland accident was perceived by many to be weak. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 71.85pt; text-indent:-43.5pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 71.85pt; text-indent:-43.5pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">5.2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The HSSG has no wish to become a pseudo-regulator – this role can only be performed by the UK CAA.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> It is, therefore, critically important for the CAA to assume a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">very strong leadership role at all times, and to ensure that messaging and directions were clear and unequivocal, especially following incidents and accidents. The operators want to see the CAA offer clearer leadership to ensure the industry respect the re</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">gulatory framework established in the UK. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 71.85pt; text-indent:-43.5pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 71.85pt; text-indent:-43.5pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">5.3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Overall the message is one of support for the CAA and for them to take a higher profile role in respect of rotary operations as they have been doing successfully in the UK for fixed-wing operations for many y</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ears.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 71.85pt; text-indent:-43.5pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">5.4</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">There is concern in the industry that EASA appear to be even more distant, even though they are taking over responsibility for much of the activity previously conducted by CAA.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 71.85pt; text-indent:-43.5pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 71.85pt; text-indent:-43.5pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>